The incident occurred on Thursday afternoon after the boy apparently suffered a neck injury. CAPE TOWN - A 15-year-old boy has died following a school rugby match in Villiersdorp, in the Western Cape. The incident occurred on Thursday afternoon after the boy apparently suffered a neck injury. The police's Noloyiso Rwexana said: “A death inquest case has been opened for investigation following the death of the 15-year-old boy. A post-mortem will be conducted to determine the cause of death.” It’s understood the teen, who was identified as Benwill Adelaar, attended Albert Myburgh Secondary School in Bredasdorp, also in the Western Cape. Members of the community have expressed heartfelt condolences to the boy’s family and friends. Rus in vrede Benwill. Ons sal jou altyd onthou. Sterkte aan sy ouers en familie  Dear learners, teachers and staff of Albert Myburgh, I am sorry for your loss. I was deeply saddened by the news of...  🌻☀️A Beautiful soul💖🕊️

